A woman police constable from Estcourt was found dead in her car on the R103 on Saturday. Police on routine patrol at about 11.15pm spotted a vehicle along the side of the road. On closer inspection they discovered the body of a woman who sustained a gunshot wound to the head. According to police, the deceased woman was identified as a constable from Estcourt police station. “Her details have not yet been released since we are awaiting her family to arrive so they can identify her officially. The case is under investigation,” said police.